				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$13.3$$\end{document} compared to the plain harvester. The idea presented here is a simple solution to use inexpensive PZT buzzers in large-scale vibration energy harvesting. This concept can remarkably reduce the cost of power and simultaneously enhance the level of available power in self-powered multi-sensor monitoring systems.

